NBMYQ4fsDXauk79yGjLXnA.text: European restaurant in Dempsey Hill.Lovely open ambience both indoor and outdoor. The food is solid good across the board but nothing particularly special. Had their signature truffle pizza, meatball rigatoni, roasted cod, several appetizers and dessert. All good but no wow factor - expected a bit more from a Jean Georges affiliated restaurant.Service is a bit slow but accommodating (i.e. one of my friends asked for a few customized dishes and they are happy to arrange)

IxcCToul5AzorbNt1I0MiA.text: Date night for two on a Saturday. Only scored an outdoor seating table at 9pm when reservation was made on Friday (poor planning on our part). But when we got there we asked if there were any indoor seating and we got one! We had:Burrata with Meyer lemon jam (fantastic combination, though the lemon did overwhelm burrata quite a bit. Burrata wasn't first rate, but the lemon helped cover its flaws)Fois gras /black olives /apple purée (super combination! Didn't think olives would work but it did)Fried calamari (just ok)Mains of:Meatball pasta (good depth)Baked cod (with coconut cream sauce. It was delicious)And dessert:Salted Caramel ice cream and popcorn (very very rich)Warm chocolate cake (good)Service was very good,And ambience was beautiful. With two cocktails, total bill was less than S$250 which isn't so bad. We were stuffedWill return!

COj2doDSjs_lUMNFe5cJew.text: Elegant modern décor. The food is good, but absolutely nothing to scream about. Service is friendly and polite, although it is a bit mechanical and lacks charm: our cold appetisers were served barely 5 minutes after the order was taken; precisely 5 minutes after we paid our bill, the waiter asked us to move to the bar to make room for the next service. At over $120++ per pax, it is not great value. Essentially, you pay  a hefty premium for the brand.

DzWojongL98eZh2oCkQ8dw.text: Beautiful space loved the interior design especially the floor. We sat at the bar and had a late lunch. The three course lunch was not too heavy I had the pea soup and the steak. They were prepared well but I cant say there was anything special. My dessert was a tart with meringue on top it was huge and too sweet for me - I had 1/4 of it. The staff was great!

W-BuakPWT961_Uk4AyN2bw.text: I got here an hour early for dinner with some friends and had the pleasure of sitting at the bar and watching these maestros work.  The bar tending team here was very knowledgeable, engaging, and a joy to watch work.This place has really mastered the art of combining classic cocktails with local fresh herbs to take things to a whole new level.  The added bonus is that the aesthetic sense of the place and how they serve their creations is really remarkable - I got schooled in the art of tweezer work in cocktail construction.  If you are out on a date and looking to impress (without the tacky flaming tiki drink kind of thing) I recommend sitting at the bar at Cookhouse.  Works of art being served all night long.My favorite part of the evening was when I ordered a negroni and asked what gin the bartender would suggest (I noticed the bar was stocked with many unique brands).  After a several minute discussion on the pros and cons of various styles - herbal, junipery, flowery) - he recommended the wonderful craft gin which made a delightful cocktail.  Sold, these guys are awesome.Oh, by the way, the food was terrific as well.  We had a lovely dinner (accompanied by another Negroni) of Veal Milanese (light, crisp, flavorful) and Roasted Cod (super light and super delicious, plenty of herbaly coconut goodness).  The room was great - big, bright and boisterous (but not too loud).  This is a place to have a fun evening out with some friends.  We loved it.

iYisFn4Z0ErItrcLhtGVng.text: A great find hidden in Dempsey hill. Perfect for late night food! The ambience and setting is very nice and the food is surprisingly very tasty. The wine collection is great as well and we tried the South African white wine on the list.

uAzJy0rsnAfu342HnzlSKw.text: Great food in beautiful setting, and good value to top it off. Been here several times, service is always consistently attentive. Didn't take any pics but the (free!) bread is such a killer it's guaranteed to end your no carb regimen. I'm not a truffle fan but the truffle pizza is peerless. Does JGV have a secret Italian godmother?!

MVPzmTOoUIVAbXUeLsHdEQ.text: I know it's Jean George and all, and the interior design and deco is very very pretty. But the food is just ok. I got the egg caviar which I liked and a burger for lunch which was ok. It just wasn't very memorable. I guess people come here for the gram where the food/place looks better than it tastes.
